trans-unit.source: Represents a security token that is based upon a Kerberos ticket that is received in a SOAP message.
trans-unit.target: Representerer en sikkerhetskode som er basert på en Kerberos-billetten som er mottatt i en SOAP-melding.

trans-unit.source: Typically, application developers do not need to use the KerberosReceiverSecurityToken class.
trans-unit.target: Utviklere programmer trenger vanligvis ikke å bruke KerberosReceiverSecurityToken-klassen.

trans-unit.source: There are two classes that represent security tokens that are based upon a Kerberos ticket: <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken> and KerberosReceiverSecurityToken.
trans-unit.target: Det er to klasser som representerer sikkerhetstokener som er basert på en Kerberos-billett: <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken>og KerberosReceiverSecurityToken.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken> security token is used by clients that use the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken> security token in outgoing SOAP messages, whereas the KerberosReceiverSecurityToken security token is used by a Web service that receives SOAP messages that contain the security token.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken>sikkerhetskode brukes av klienter som bruker den <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken>sikkerhetstoken i utgående SOAP meldinger, mens KerberosReceiverSecurityToken Sikkerhetstokenet brukes av en webtjeneste som mottar SOAP-meldinger som inneholder sikkerhetstokenet.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken> </xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken>
